{
  "texts": [
    "Based on these findings, we propose the following strategic recommendations for the future development of the field.",
    "For practitioners, prioritizing the construction of an \"LLM + Iterative Refinement\" architecture, which is currently the optimal solution for addressing the low usability issue.",
    "In terms of research focus, attention must shift from mere coverage improvement to the enhancement of semantic validity, specifically tackling the core challenge of test oracle generation.",
    "At the community level, there is an urgent need to establish a decontaminated, multi-lingual, and multi-domain standardized evaluation ecosystem to replace superficial textual similarity metrics with dynamic execution-based metrics.By addressing these challenges and seizing these opportunities, LLMs hold the promise of transcending the role of auxiliary tools to become a fundamental component of modern software quality assurance.Fig. 1.1Fig.",
    "Overview of the paper collection process."
  ]
}